{
  "message": "fuzz(csv_parse): seed corpus with 10 structured CSV inputs\n\nExtend the fuzz_csv_parse corpus from 4 tracked seeds (mostly\nedge-case shapes) with 10 hand-curated structured seeds that\nbroaden coverage across the fp-io CSV reader's parsing surface.\nEach seed is a real, plausible CSV document \u2014 small enough that\nlibFuzzer's mutator can productively transform it, and shaped to\nexercise a specific parser branch:\n\nValid inputs (the parser must accept):\n  - bool_null_valid_seed.csv      bool + nullable mixed column\n  - embedded_quotes_valid_seed.csv \"\" inside a quoted field\n  - empty_fields_valid_seed.csv    leading/trailing empty fields,\n                                    multiple consecutive commas,\n                                    a fully-empty row\n  - header_only_seed.csv           header row but zero data rows\n  - numeric_mixed_valid_seed.csv   ints + floats + negatives in\n                                    one column (type inference\n                                    must widen)\n  - quoted_blank_fields_seed.csv   \"\" as a literal empty string\n                                    inside quotes (vs unquoted\n                                    null sentinel)\n  - space_preserved_valid_seed.csv leading/trailing spaces inside\n                                    quotes preserved verbatim\n  - unquoted_text_valid_seed.csv   plain ASCII text columns,\n                                    no quoting required\n  - wide_four_cols_valid_seed.csv  wider 4-column row to exercise\n                                    multi-column dispatch paths\n\nInvalid inputs (the parser must reject \u2014 but without panic):\n  - ragged_extra_field_invalid_seed.csv\n                                    a row with one extra field\n                                    beyond the header arity\n\nThese complement the existing 4 seeds (duplicate_headers_invalid,\nquoted_newline_valid, ragged_extra_field_invalid, seed-empty)\nand bring the total tracked corpus to 14, giving libFuzzer a\nbetter starting distribution before mutation kicks in.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
